This paper deals with resource allocation in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization and mathematical modeling, which suggests that it could also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) or systems and control (cs.SY) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions femto/pico cells, which are a type of mobile computing, and TV white spaces, which are a type of multimedia communication, indicating that it could also belong to the categories of multimedia (cs.MM) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
